# Architecture

## Service boundaries

| Layer | Responsibility | Must NOT do |
|-------|----------------|-------------|
| **n8n** | Cron, retries, workflow coordination | Business logic, DB writes, scraping |
| **Backend** | Business logic, DB, AI calls, decisions | Browser automation, cron orchestration |
| **Playwright** | Login, clicks, read/send DOM actions | Filtering, AI, scheduling decisions |
| **LLM** | Text generation (letters, chat replies) | Side effects, DB, browser |
| **Web** | Read-only ops UI (queue, applications) | Business logic, DB, Playwright, mutations |

## Process requirements

Every workflow/use case must be:

- **Independent** — can run without other workers
- **Restartable** — safe after crash/redeploy
- **Idempotent** — same input → same outcome (no duplicate applies)
- **Observable** — logs, status fields, health endpoints

## Request flow

```
Browser (apps/web) → Backend API (read)
n8n → Backend API (use case) → Playwright / LLM / DB
```
